MEDIA personality Somizi Mhlongo is like a cat with nine lives, and he never fails to redeem himself no matter how big the scandal is. The media personality, who was canned by Idols SA following abuse allegations, is back on the judging panel. He will be joined by singer and actress Thembi Seete and rapper JR. Co-executive producer Tebogo “ProVerb” Thekisho will return to host the music competition for its 13th season. ALSO READ | MR AND MRS JONES PART WAYS In a statement Nomsa Philiso, executive head of programming for general entertainment at M-Net, said they are excited about the return of the show. “We have such longevity in such a fast-changing industry and we’re proud to keep giving our viewers what they love. One of the key components in having staying power is evolution, and our new-look panel is part of that,” she said. “Idols SA is an important part of our creative industry. Not only do we unearth hidden talent, but we also nurture our contestants and equip them with the necessary tools to start or grow their careers. It’s a privilege to be able to do that for another season.”